DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Percent Free Prostate-Specific Antigen Outcome Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The result of the free prostate-specific antigen (PSA) procedure.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Percent Free Prostate-Specific Antigen Outcome
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the outcome of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood, urine, or other substance from the body for prostate-specific antigen that circulates freely in the blood, unattached to any protein molecule.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: PSA circulates in the blood in two forms: free or attached to a protein molecule.  With benign prostate conditions, there is more free PSA, while cancer produces more of the attached form.  A more accurate predictor of cancer than either a patient's age or his total PSA level. (from Cancer Information Service):Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.
